  <Docs>
    <summary>Specifies arguments for selecting and configuring a font within a font collection.</summary>
    <remarks><format type="text/markdown"><![CDATA[
## Remarks

`SKFontArguments` lets you specify which font to use from a font collection (via `CollectionIndex`), which color palette to apply (`PaletteIndex`), optional palette color overrides (`PaletteOverrides`), and a variation design position (`VariationDesignPosition`).

## Examples

```csharp
var args = new SKFontArguments { CollectionIndex = 0, PaletteIndex = 1 };
using var typeface = original.Clone(args);
```
]]></format></remarks>
  </Docs>
